After his rise to fame, it has been a difficult few years for TV chef Gordon Ramsay.

He reportedly paid his father-in-law £2million to end a long-running row over his business in 2012.

The pair went their separate way after Ramsay accused Chris Hutcheson of taking money out of parent company Gordon Ramsay Holdings (GRH).

He was even seen in an awkward QVC pitch, as he tried to sell the 'Nonstick Hard Anodized Dishwasher Safe 10-piece Cookware Set'.

