Also in 2009, he sold his restaurant in Prague – Maze at the Hilton in Prague’s Old Town – back to the hotel.

The father-of-four closed two eateries in Australia in 2011, waving goodbye to Maze and Maze Grill in Melbourne’s Crown Metropol Hotel.

Further troubles include a £1.1million court battle in New Zealand after pulling out of a number of charity engagements, citing personal reasons

Even wife Tana tried to help pocket some cash after agreeing to star on the fifth series of British Dancing On Ice, but soap star Hayley Tamaddon triumphed as the winner.

Ramsay’s rise to fame led from restaurant kitchens to Hollywood.

He began with Restaurant Gordon Ramsay, which won three coveted Michelin stars in 2001.

Then his empire expanded quickly, with Amaryllis in Glasgow, Gordon Ramsay at Claridge’s, and eateries in Dubai, Tokyo and New York.

From Royal Doulton to Kmart, from Argos to the QVC shopping channel, you are never far away from Gordon Ramsay-branded products.

All this helped Gordon Ramsay Holdings to a turnover of £4.8 million in 2011, although expenses and bad debts lead to heavy losses.  In that year he also opened a new restaurant in London.  In 2012 he opened four new restaurants in the US.

